<img src="/resources/cce3b4ab8b5422578e0b58a54c2b976b46e231a0/CNX_Calc_Figure_02_03_202.jpg" data-media-type="image/jpeg" alt="The graph of a piecewise function with two segments. The first is the parabola x^2, which exists for x&lt;=3. The vertex is at the origin, it opens upward, and there is a closed circle at the endpoint (3,9). The second segment is the line x+4, which is a linear function existing for x &gt; 3. There is an open circle at (3, 7), and the slope is 1."/>
