</p><span data-type="media" id="fs-id1170572268051" data-alt="The graph of a piecewise function with two segments. The first segment is the parabola x^2 &#8211; 2x + 1, for x &lt; 2. It opens upward and has a vertex at (1,0). The second segment is the line 3-x for x&gt;= 2. It has a slope of -1 and an x intercept at (3,0).">
<img src="/resources/3edd9864e059dcffdf0a0c76112802fc934432da/CNX_Calc_Figure_02_03_204.jpg" data-media-type="image/jpeg" alt="The graph of a piecewise function with two segments. The first segment is the parabola x^2 &#8211; 2x + 1, for x &lt; 2. It opens upward and has a vertex at (1,0). The second segment is the line 3-x for x&gt;= 2. It has a slope of -1 and an x intercept at (3,0)."/>
</span><p><span data-type="newline"><br/></span>
a. 1; b. 1</p>
</div>
